The paper discusses a machine learning approach to tackle the problem of insufficient training data, which is a common issue in various subfields of computer science. The paper specifically focuses on vision classification and semantic segmentation tasks, which are typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) subfields. The suggested approach involves using confidence assessments to improve the training process, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of deep learning (cs.DL) methods, which are commonly used in computer vision and natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.DL.
